just_use critters.go

# label: EARLY
# role: supports feature — critter-study metadata + telemetry intake

CRITTER_STUDIES V1 (2026-04-15). Reads study DSLs from
`critters/studies/*.claude` and provides a minimal Study index for
the portal. Accepts telemetry payloads from the Elm engine's
saveRecording port and stores each session as a row in
critter_sessions (payload kept as raw JSON; study + label lifted
for indexing).

Gopher only parses `title:` and `desc:` from the .claude; the full
DSL is the Elm engine's responsibility.

2MB body cap on telemetry to avoid accidental DoS. Study name is
derived from the filename (stable id) not the DSL contents.

V2 prototyping (2026-04-17): standalone browser prototypes for
new mechanics live under `proto/` — see `proto/README.md`. The
current iteration adds indirect manipulation (human drags a dog,
dog pressures cows). When a prototype graduates, it moves into
the Elm engine or gets its own study DSL under `studies/`.
